      • createSafeZone

        public static SafeZones.SafeZoneCreate createSafeZone(org.bukkit.entity.Player player,
                                      java.lang.String pluginName,
                                      java.lang.String zoneName)
        Parameters:
        player - This player is used for the location and for the permissions checks.
        If the player is not allowed to build in a WorldGuard region, or if he is not on the managers list in a GriefPrevention claim, it will return with NoPermission.

        pluginName - The name of the plugin you want to use to create the safezone.
        Can be "griefprevention" or "worldguard". (Case Insensitive)

        zoneName - The name you want the safeZone to have.
        Duplicate names are not allowed. (Will return SafeZoneCreate.AlreadyExists)

        Returns:
        The reason why the creation succeeded or failed.

      • removeSafeZone

        public static boolean removeSafeZone(TRSafeZone zone)
        Removes a WorldGuard/GriefPrevention safezone from the database.
        Do not use this method in a loop. It will cause ConcurrentModificationExceptions.
        Returns:
        True if the removal succeeded. False otherwise.

      • getSafeZoneByLocation

        public static java.lang.String getSafeZoneByLocation(org.bukkit.Location location,
                                     boolean checkGP)
        Searches for a WorldGuard safezone in the database for the given location. If checkGP is true, it will also check for GriefPrevention Safezones.
        Returns:
        "" if none is found. A message with more information about the safezone otherwise.

      • getSafeZoneFor

        public static java.lang.String getSafeZoneFor(org.bukkit.entity.Player player)
        Get a safezone at the players current position that applies to him.
        First checks GriefPrevention, then WorldGuard, Towny, Factions and last PreciousStones.
        Returns:
        "" If none is found/none applies. A string with information about the safezone otherwise.
        See Also:
        getSafeZoneFor(Player, List)
